Variable x:𝖤𝗅𝖾𝗆𝖾𝗇𝗍

Variable 𝒞:𝖢𝗈𝗅𝗅𝖾𝖼𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇

Theorem (NegatedMembership)
  x ∉ 𝒞 𝗂𝖿𝖿 ¬(x ∈ 𝒞)
  Proof
    ¬(x is an element of 𝒞) 𝗂𝖿𝖿 x ∉ 𝒞 by NonMembership
    x is an element of 𝒞 𝗂𝖿𝖿 x ∈ 𝒞 by Membership
    ¬(x is an element of 𝒞) 𝗂𝖿𝖿 ¬(x ∈ 𝒞) by BiconditionalContrapositive
  Therefore
    x ∉ 𝒞 𝗂𝖿𝖿 ¬(x ∈ 𝒞) by TransitiveBiconditional
